programme.desc: The No. 8 Buckeyes play the No. 1 Ducks in the Rose Bowl College Football Playoff quarterfinal. Ohio State drubbed No. 9 Tennessee 42-17 on Dec. 21. Oregon shaved Ohio State 32-31 on Oct. 12. Oregons Dillon Gabriel finished third in Heisman voting.

programme.title: The Buddy Way
programme.desc: The historic life and career of Coach Eugene F. "Buddy" Teevens III, highlighting his championship successes as a multi-sport athlete, his pivotal role at the Manning Passing Academy, and the groundbreaking innovations he made on and off the field.

programme.title: 30 for 30
programme.desc: This documentary film takes a close look at the creation of a legend -- two-sport athlete Vincent Edward "Bo" Jackson, the only person ever selected to play in the NFL Pro Bowl and the MLB All-Star Game.

programme.title: The Climb: LSU Gymnastics
programme.desc: An in-depth look at the LSU gymnastics program.

programme.title: E60
programme.desc: ESPNs morning sports magazine show, featuring the biggest names and stories in sports.

programme.title: 30 for 30
programme.desc: Director Rory Karpf, through interviews with former players and rivals as well as Laettner himself, explores why this former Duke star was, and still is, so disliked.

programme.title: ESPN Films
programme.sub-title: The Class That Saved Coach K
programme.desc: The story of Duke basketball head coach Mike Krzyzewski and his 1982 recruiting class that, over four years, would overcome a bumpy start to change the narrative - setting its coach on a historic course.

programme.title: Were #1! -- 1991 and 1992 Duke Blue Devils
programme.desc: Through a mix of archival footage, photographs, game broadcasts and exclusive interviews, Were #1! looks back at the memorable Duke teams that defined an era of college basketball.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: In the aftermath of the Civil War, Americas South is looking to put the past behind it, and finds one path in a growing cultural passion of the North - football. In December 1932, the Southeastern Conference is officially formed.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: Multiple SEC schools claim national titles from the 1930s through the 50s, including LSU with star running back Billy Cannon in 1958, prior to Cannons epic game-winning punt return against powerhouse Ole Miss a year later.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: In the 1960s, as Georgia Tech leaves the conference and the Civil Rights Movement becomes embedded in the history and image of the region, Bear Bryant, hired in 1958, becomes the face of Alabama - and SEC football.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: As a new decade dawns, quarterbacks Archie Manning, Bert Jones and Condredge Holloway build memorable legacies. Bear Bryant begins a new run of dominance at Alabama, and the rise of television sports transforms the SEC.

programme.title: Unsportsmanlike with Evan, Canty and Michelle
programme.desc: Start the day off right with Chris Canty, Evan Cohen and Michelle Smallmon providing an energizing and informative way to take on the day. Sports, life and laughter are what its all about.

programme.title: Playoff Quarterfinal at the Rose Bowl Game

programme.title: Playoff Semifinal at the Goodyear Cotton Bowl Classic
programme.desc: The No. 8 Buckeyes burst into their CFP semifinal against the No. 5 Longhorns in the Cotton Bowl. Ohio State routed No. 1 Oregon 41-21 in the quarters. Texas coughed up a 16-point lead before surviving No. 4 Arizona State 39-31 in double overtime.

programme.title: CFP National Championship
programme.desc: The No. 7 Fighting Irish (14-1) battle the No. 8 Buckeyes (13-2) in the College Football Playoff final from Atlanta. Notre Dame seeks a 12th championship but the first for the storied school since 1988, while Ohio State aims for its ninth title.

programme.title: The Matrix Resurrections
programme.desc: If Mr. Anderson, aka Neo, has learned anything, its that choice, while an illusion, is the only way out of -- or into -- the Matrix. Neo knows what he has to do, but what he doesnt yet know is that the Matrix is now stronger and far more dangerous.

programme.title: Daddys Home
programme.desc: An insecure man (Will Ferrell) competes for the affection of his stepchildren when their freewheeling father (Mark Wahlberg) breezes back into town.

programme.title: The Italian Job
programme.desc: A master thief (Mark Wahlberg) and his crew plan to steal back a fortune in gold bullion after they lose it to a double-crossing gang member (Edward Norton).

programme.title: Shooter
programme.desc: Reluctantly pressed into service again, a former military sniper (Mark Wahlberg) plots revenge against his powerful foes after being betrayed and wounded.

programme.title: Sniper: Ghost Shooter
programme.desc: Elite snipers Beckett (Chad Michael Collins) and Miller (Billy Zane) are tasked with guarding a gas pipeline. A ghost shooter seems to know exactly where theyll be at all times, and they begin to suspect hes being aided from within.

programme.title: Sniper: Assassins End
programme.desc: On the run from the CIA, special ops sniper Brandon Beckett and his legendary father take on Russian mercenaries and a yakuza-trained assassin.

programme.title: Hollywood One on One
programme.desc: Hollywood celebrities give insight into their personal and professional lives, and open up about upcoming projects.

programme.title: Taxi 3
programme.desc: A cabdriver (Samy Naceri) and a policeman (Frederic Diefenthal) pursue a gang of Chinese criminals committing robberies throughout France.

programme.title: Badges of Fury
programme.desc: Two troublemaking cops investigate eerie murders and find a link to an aspiring starlet.

programme.title: Red
programme.desc: Retired CIA agents (Bruce Willis, Morgan Freeman, John Malkovich) reassemble for survival after the agency sends assassins to silence them and the secrets they carry.

programme.title: Red 2
programme.desc: Former CIA black-ops agent Frank Moses (Bruce Willis) and his team battle assassins, terrorists and power-hungry government officials as they try to retrieve a lethal device that could change the balance of world power.

programme.title: I Spy
programme.desc: A special agent (Owen Wilson) and a boxing champion (Eddie Murphy) travel to Budapest, Hungary, to locate an arms dealer and a stealth bomber.

programme.title: The Fighter
programme.desc: Having earned a shot at a world championship, boxer Micky Ward (Mark Wahlberg) reunites with his estranged brother (Christian Bale) to train for the fight and become the new "Pride of Lowell."

programme.desc: An insecure man (Will Ferrell) competes for the affection of his stepchildren when their freewheeling father (Mark Wahlberg) breezes back into town.

programme.desc: Reluctantly pressed into service again, a former military sniper (Mark Wahlberg) plots revenge against his powerful foes after being betrayed and wounded.

programme.desc: In the mountains of Afghanistan, a squad of Taliban fighters ambushes four Navy SEALs, who are there on a mission to eliminate a high-ranking al-Qaeda operative.

programme.title: Tears of the Sun
programme.desc: A Navy SEAL (Bruce Willis) and his squad try to protect a doctor (Monica Bellucci) and Nigerian refugees from ruthless rebels.

programme.title: Hunted
programme.desc: A young woman is trapped in a game of cat and mouse after she meets a charming man at a nightclub.

programme.title: I Think Were Alone Now
programme.desc: After a catastrophe destroys most of humanity, a recluse lives in his small, empty town, content with the utopia hes methodically created for himself -- until an interloper disrupts his solitude.

programme.title: Warrior
programme.desc: An Iraq War veteran (Tom Hardy) finds himself on a collision course with his estranged brother (Joel Edgerton) when both set their sights on winning a tournament in mixed martial arts.

programme.title: The Intruder
programme.desc: A couple buy their dream home from a lonely widower in the California countryside. When he starts to interfere in their daily lives, they soon find themselves caught up in a violent confrontation that threatens to destroy everything they hold dear.
